  <section>
    <h2>About this page</h2>
    <p>This is a community resource, not an official source. It was put together by Russell Jones, a Sagamok Anishnawbek member, on behalf of the Ontario Indigenous AI &amp; Technology Council (OIATC). It is not affiliated with Potentia Renewables, the Township of Sables-Spanish Rivers, the Massey Wildlife Conservation Committee, or any First Nation including Sagamok.</p>
    <p>The goal is to help residents and First Nations members on the North Shore hold the five moving pieces apart, see what has been decided and what is still ahead, and find the primary sources if they want to dig deeper. People are capable of drawing their own conclusions; the page does not take a side on whether the project should be built, or on whether the Indigenous partnership as currently structured is adequate.</p>
    <p>If you spot something that needs correction, or you have a question this page doesn't answer, please email <a href="mailto:jonesrussell42@gmail.com">jonesrussell42@gmail.com</a>. Suggestions for additions welcome.</p>
